            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_002379_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U">28</add> <space extent="2" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U">72</add></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><date when="1865-07-30">30 July 1865</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><placeName><hi rend="blue black small" resp="#U2">NEWSTEAD ABBEY,
<lb/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small">Acc 5973</add> <space extent="2" unit="words"/>MANSFIELD.
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/>NOTTS.</hi></placeName></p> <!-- Is this correct? It doesn't show up, but I'm not sure if it's supposed to? SF --><!-- Would be OK either way, actually, but looks better with it in. -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Hamilton</p><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><p>Many thanks
<lb/>for the parcel
<lb/><choice><sic>recieved</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> this 
<lb/>morning - I did
<lb/>not know that 
<lb/>I had left the collars
<lb/>though I thought
<lb/>I had left some
<lb/>for <persName>Agnes</persName> to <w><subst><del>g</del><add place="over-text">s</add></subst>end</w><!-- Not sure if this is right, but it looks to me like he wrote "send", but perhaps started to write "give"? SF -->
<lb/>to the <unclear cert="medium"><term type="occupation">washerwoman</term></unclear>

	<pb facs="liv_002379_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><persName>Oswell</persName> was upset 
<lb/>about the train
<lb/>and we were just
<lb/>in time. <persName>Webb</persName> is 
<lb/>better - we have 
<lb/><persName>Shelley</persName> &amp; <persName>Oswell</persName>
<lb/>&amp; <term type="nationality">African</term> &amp;
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">rocky</unclear> mountain
<lb/>talk has driven 
<lb/>out the pains &amp;
<lb/>he walks about
<lb/>quite brisk - <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi>
<lb/>Webb</persName> was giving

	<pb facs="liv_002379_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>me a scolding this <add place="above" rend="gray" hand="#U">73</add>
<lb/>morning for the
<lb/>going on Tuesday
<lb/>next - she thought
<lb/>I was to be here
<lb/>till starting on 
<lb/>the <date when="1865-08-11">11<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date> I shall
<lb/>go to <placeName><settlement type="town">Sedgwick</settlement></placeName> on
<lb/>Wednesday &amp;
<lb/>pack up on Friday
<lb/>on which night
<lb/>you had better
<lb/>write your friends
<lb/>as must come
<lb/>back - on Saturday

	<pb facs="liv_002379_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>they are going to
<lb/>keep <persName>Agnes</persName> so 
<lb/>I must come
<lb/>back</p>
<lb/><p>I wonder if 
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">s</hi> Binney</persName>
<lb/>would come on
<lb/>that <unclear cert="low">upset</unclear> for it
<lb/>will be impossible
<lb/>for me to go to
<lb/>him for which
<lb/>I am sorry</p>

<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="words"/>I am &amp;c<!-- Change as appropriate -->
<lb/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p><!-- Change as appropriate --><!-- I can't get this signature to go to the left... I've tried rend="left" but with no luck. SF --> 



